---
/**
 * Sidebar.astro -- astro-shad app sidebar. Converted from shadcn
 * ui/sidebar.tsx (the SidebarProvider/Sidebar/useIsMobile/useSidebar
 * stack, ~720 lines). React's job there was almost entirely state
 * plumbing (open/collapsed/mobile) through context -- all three collapse
 * to DOM state here:
 *
 * - open/collapsed lives as `data-state` on this component's own root,
 *   read by children via `group-data-[state=collapsed]/sidebar:*`
 *   (Tailwind arbitrary group variant) -- no context, no prop drilling.
 * - mobile vs desktop is NOT a JS media-query (useIsMobile deleted
 *   entirely): both the desktop `<aside>` (`hidden md:flex`) and a mobile
 *   `<Sheet>` wrapping the SAME slotted content (`md:hidden`) render in
 *   the DOM; the breakpoint is CSS `display`, so exactly one is ever
 *   visible. `header`/default/`footer` slot content is needed in BOTH
 *   places -- literally repeating `<slot>` tags for this turned out to be
 *   unreliable in practice (Astro's "render a slot again" escape hatch,
 *   `data-astro-rerun`, plus multiple same-named-slot siblings on the
 *   caller side, hit several compounding edge cases -- astro#17266 and
 *   related). Sidestepped entirely: each slot is rendered to an HTML
 *   string exactly ONCE via `Astro.slots.render()` in the frontmatter
 *   below, then `set:html` puts that string DIRECTLY on the real wrapper
 *   `<div>` in both the desktop and mobile markup -- no `<slot>` tag
 *   appears more than once anywhere in this file, and no `<Fragment>`
 *   indirection either (`set:html` on a `<Fragment>` proved unreliable
 *   paired with `Astro.slots.render()` -- a real DOM node is what
 *   `set:html` wants). Each wrapper only renders when its slot actually
 *   has content (`{headerHtml && <div .../>}`) -- replaces the
 *   `empty:hidden` CSS trick, which doesn't reliably catch this case
 *   (line-break whitespace between tags can keep a div out of `:empty`).
 *   Trade-off, stated plainly: header/content/footer content still exists
 *   TWICE in the HTML (once per branch) -- fine for nav markup (links,
 *   buttons), a poor fit for anything with client state or a
 *   crypto.randomUUID()-based id that must be unique per page (e.g. two
 *   <Combobox> instances with the same name would each render twice).
 * - `SidebarTrigger` drives both branches from one click: it flips this
 *   root's `data-state`, then click()s the mobile Sheet's own hidden
 *   trigger span so Sheet's existing open logic runs unchanged. Harmless
 *   on desktop -- the whole mobile branch is `md:hidden`, so the Sheet
 *   opening there is invisible.
 *
 * `variant` ("sidebar" default | "floating" | "inset") matches shadcn's
 * three looks: "sidebar" is a flush edge-to-edge rail with a border;
 * "floating" adds padding around a rounded/ring/shadow inner card;
 * "inset" looks the same as "sidebar" on its own but tells `SidebarInset`
 * (via a `peer`/`peer-data-[variant=inset]` relationship -- see below) to
 * render the main content as its own inset rounded card instead of full
 * width. The draggable resize `SidebarRail` (shadcn's collapse-by-drag
 * handle) is still dropped -- decorative, not core, addable later if a
 * design calls for it.
 *
 * "inset"'s illusion (one continuous page, a white card floating inset
 * on all four sides) depends on a PAGE-LEVEL choice this component can't
 * make for you: give your own outer wrapper `bg-sidebar` (not the
 * default `bg-background`), so the color around `SidebarInset`'s margin
 * matches the `<aside>` itself -- the aside then visually blends into
 * "the page" and only `SidebarInset`'s card (still `bg-background`)
 * reads as distinct. Collapsed, this is also why the aside appears to
 * "disappear": it's still there physically (an icon rail, or nothing at
 * all under `collapsible="offcanvas"`), just the same flat color as
 * everything around it.
 *
 *   <div class="flex min-h-svh bg-sidebar">
 *     <Sidebar variant="inset">...</Sidebar>
 *     <SidebarInset>...</SidebarInset>
 *   </div>
 * `collapsible="none"` renders an always-expanded, non-collapsing aside
 * (no mobile Sheet needed either, since there's nothing to toggle).
 *
 * The `peer`/`peer-data-*` link to `SidebarInset` needs a REAL DOM
 * sibling, not the inner `<aside>` -- this component's own root
 * (`data-astro-shad-sidebar-root`) is `display:contents` precisely so it
 * doesn't add a layout box, but it's still the literal DOM sibling of
 * `<SidebarInset>` in consumer markup, so `peer`/`data-variant`/
 * `data-state` live there. `SidebarTrigger` keeps that root's
 * `data-state` in sync with the `<aside>`'s on every toggle (both are
 * updated together), so `SidebarInset`'s `peer-data-[state=collapsed]`
 * margin adjustment (inset variant only) never goes stale.
 *
 *   <div class="flex min-h-svh">
 *     <Sidebar>
 *       <div slot="header">...brand...</div>
 *       <SidebarGroup label="Platform">
 *         <SidebarMenuButton href="/create" active>
 *           <Icon slot="icon" name="lucide:layout-grid" />Create
 *         </SidebarMenuButton>
 *       </SidebarGroup>
 *       <div slot="footer">...user menu...</div>
 *     </Sidebar>
 *     <SidebarInset>
 *       <SidebarTrigger />
 *       ...page content...
 *     </SidebarInset>
 *   </div>
 *
 * `header`/`footer` are raw slots -- Sidebar.astro imposes no structure on
 * them (unlike `SidebarMenuButton`'s dedicated `icon` slot + auto-hiding
 * label). If your header/footer content is a brand row or a user row
 * (mark + text label), apply the SAME collapse convention
 * `SidebarMenuButton` uses internally, by hand: leave the mark (svg / img
 * / styled span badge -- whatever it is) bare so it keeps showing at any
 * width, and add `class="group-data-[state=collapsed]/sidebar:hidden"`
 * to the text label so it disappears instead of wrapping/smushing in the
 * 3rem icon rail. A one-class convention beats a dedicated slot API here
 * since it works identically regardless of what the mark element is.
 *
 *   <div slot="header" class="flex items-center gap-2 group-data-[state=collapsed]/sidebar:justify-center">
 *     <span class="grid size-6 shrink-0 place-items-center rounded-md bg-sidebar-primary text-sidebar-primary-foreground">A</span>
 *     <span class="truncate group-data-[state=collapsed]/sidebar:hidden">astro-shad</span>
 *   </div>
 *
 * Need more than one piece of content in `footer` (e.g. a quick-links
 * group ABOVE a user row)? Put both inside one `<div slot="footer"
 * class="contents">` rather than giving each element its own
 * `slot="footer"` -- several separate same-named-slot siblings hits an
 * open Astro edge case (astro#17266) where only one ends up rendering.
 * A real DOM node (not `<Fragment>`) matters here too -- this repo's
 * `Astro.slots.render()` usage above only picked up a Fragment-wrapped
 * slot's content unreliably; `class="contents"` (`display: contents`)
 * keeps the wrapper out of the layout tree, so it costs nothing visually:
 *
 *   <div slot="footer" class="contents">
 *     <SidebarGroup label="Projects">...</SidebarGroup>
 *     <div class="flex items-center gap-2 px-2 py-1.5">...user row...</div>
 *   </div>
 */
import { cn } from "../../lib/utils";
import Sheet from "./Sheet.astro";

interface Props {
  side?: "left" | "right";
  variant?: "sidebar" | "floating" | "inset";
  collapsible?: "icon" | "offcanvas" | "none";
  defaultOpen?: boolean;
  class?: string;
  [key: string]: unknown;
}

const { side = "left", variant = "sidebar", collapsible = "icon", defaultOpen = true, class: className, ...rest } = Astro.props;

const state = defaultOpen ? "expanded" : "collapsed";
const padded = variant === "floating" || variant === "inset";

/* Every branch must appear as a complete literal string in this file for
   Tailwind's static scanner to pick it up -- a template-literal-built
   class name would never match. */
const COLLAPSE_CLASS =
  collapsible === "offcanvas"
    ? "data-[state=collapsed]:w-0 data-[state=collapsed]:overflow-hidden data-[state=collapsed]:border-transparent data-[state=collapsed]:p-0"
    : padded
      ? "data-[state=collapsed]:w-[calc(var(--sidebar-width-icon)+1rem)]"
      : "data-[state=collapsed]:w-(--sidebar-width-icon)";

const SIDE_BORDER_CLASS = padded ? "" : side === "left" ? "border-r border-sidebar-border" : "border-l border-sidebar-border";

/* Render each slot to an HTML string exactly once -- see the header
   comment. Reused via set:html in both the desktop and mobile markup
   below instead of ever writing <slot> more than once. */
const headerHtml = await Astro.slots.render("header");
const contentHtml = await Astro.slots.render("default");
const footerHtml = await Astro.slots.render("footer");
---

<div class="peer contents" data-astro-shad-sidebar-root data-variant={variant} data-state={state} {...rest}>
  <!-- desktop -->
  <div
    data-astro-shad-sidebar
    data-state={state}
    data-side={side}
    style="--sidebar-width:16rem;--sidebar-width-icon:3rem"
    class={cn(
      "group/sidebar hidden h-full w-(--sidebar-width) shrink-0 flex-col text-sidebar-foreground transition-[width] duration-200 ease-linear md:flex",
      side === "right" && "order-last",
      padded ? "p-2" : SIDE_BORDER_CLASS,
      collapsible !== "none" && COLLAPSE_CLASS,
      className,
    )}
  >
    <div
      class={cn(
        "flex size-full flex-col bg-sidebar",
        variant === "floating" && "rounded-lg shadow-sm ring-1 ring-sidebar-border bg-accent",
      )}
    >
      {headerHtml && <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-2" set:html={headerHtml} />}

      {
        contentHtml && (
          <div
            class="no-scrollbar flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col gap-0 overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto group-data-[state=collapsed]/sidebar:overflow-hidden"
            set:html={contentHtml}
          />
        )
      }

      {footerHtml && <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 p-2" set:html={footerHtml} />}
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- mobile: same content (already-rendered strings above), inside a Sheet, CSS-hidden at md+ -->
  {
    collapsible !== "none" && (
      <div class="md:hidden">
        <Sheet side={side} title="Menu" showCloseButton={true}>
          <div class="flex h-full flex-col">
            {headerHtml && <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 pb-2" set:html={headerHtml} />}
            {contentHtml && (
              <div class="no-scrollbar flex min-h-0 flex-1 flex-col gap-0 overflow-x-hidden overflow-y-auto" set:html={contentHtml} />
            )}
            {footerHtml && <div class="flex flex-col gap-2 pt-2" set:html={footerHtml} />}
          </div>
        </Sheet>
      </div>
    )
  }
</div>
